In this article, President Trump made remarks during a press conference at the United Nations Headquarters. He discussed the situation in Venezuela, expressing his willingness to meet with its leader and help the suffering people. He also emphasized that the US is with its allies in the region and will protect them. Regarding North Korea, Trump stated that progress is being made in denuclearization and that Chairman Kim wants good things for his country. The President mentioned his good relationship with Japanese Prime Minister Abe and their discussion on trade. He also mentioned that the First Lady will be making a trip to Africa, but the specific countries she will visit will be announced later. Trump commented on the ongoing confirmation process of Judge Kavanaugh and stated that he believes Kavanaugh is outstanding and has been treated unfairly by Democrats playing a "con game."